WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.540 --> 00:00:05.820
Technologies like AliveCor have
potential uses beyond patients at home.

00:00:05.820 --> 00:00:10.216
A recent article in Circulation,
a leading heart disease journal,

00:00:10.216 --> 00:00:15.067
reported on success in using the device
to screen for atrial fibrillation,

00:00:15.067 --> 00:00:17.520
the most common cardiac arrhythmia.

00:00:17.520 --> 00:00:21.890
And one that can lead to strokes if
not identified and properly treated.

00:00:21.890 --> 00:00:23.850
If you were the FDA, how and

00:00:23.850 --> 00:00:27.740
where would you draw the line between
apps you regulate and those you don't?

